:::summary
The Roman Catholic Church is the world's largest Christian denomination and the oldest continuously existing institution in Western civilization, with approximately 1.4 billion members. It traces its origins to Jesus Christ and His Apostles and claims an unbroken line of apostolic succession from Peter, whom Catholics regard as the first pope. Its theology, sacramental system, moral teaching, and institutional history have shaped Western culture, law, philosophy, and art more deeply than any other single institution.
:::

